This assumption that nationalism must be a malign force is lazy and thoughtless, as demonstrated by Alexander Hamilton’s much celebrated career.
Hamilton advanced and, to a significant extent, defined these nationalist projects.
The most important was the first — establishing our independence from the British empire in the world’s greatest nationalist rebellion.
Then, Hamilton helped put the new national government on a firm financial foundation.
Millennials are notably less attached to the symbols of the American nation — and less drawn to patriotic pride — than their elders.